Package: cubeview
Type: Package
Title: View 3D Raster Cubes Interactively
Version: 0.1.0
Date: 2019-02-10
Authors@R: 
    c(person(given = "Tim",
             family = "Appelhans",
             role = c("cre", "aut"),
             email = "tim.appelhans@gmail.com"),
      person(given = "Stefan",
             family = "Woellauer",
             role = "aut",
             email = "stephan.woellauer@geo.uni-marburg.de"))
Maintainer: Tim Appelhans <tim.appelhans@gmail.com>
Description: Create a 3D data cube from a RasterStack or RasterBrick. 
    The cube can be freely rotated so that Hovmoller views of x - y, x - z and 
    y - z are possible. Flick through each dimension using left/right (x), 
    up/down (y) and page-up/page-down (z) buttons. 
    Zoom, pan and rotate the cube to explore different parts of the data.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Depends:
    R (>= 2.10)
Imports:
    base64enc,
    htmltools,
    htmlwidgets,
    lattice,
    raster,
    viridisLite
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 6.1.0
